<p>How can I show the month and year of the calendar that it is currently showing? To be more specific, I want it to September 2015 on the red circle.</p>  <p>Javascript:</p>  <pre><code>        var titles = new Array(),             starts = new Array(),             ends = new Array();         &lt;%             ArrayList&lt;CalendarDTO&gt; list = (ArrayList)session.getAttribute("list");             for(CalendarDTO l: list) {         %&gt;                 titles.push("&lt;%=l.getTitle()%&gt;");                 starts.push("&lt;%=l.getStart()%&gt;");                 ends.push("&lt;%=l.getEnd()%&gt;");         &lt;%}%&gt;         $('#calendar').fullCalendar({             header: {                 left: 'prev, next, today',                 center: 'title',                 right: 'month, basicWeek, basicDay'             },             editable: false,             droppable: true, // this allows things to be dropped onto the calendar !!!             drop: function(date, allDay) {              },             events: [                 &lt;%                     for(CalendarDTO c: list) {                 %&gt;                 {                     title: "&lt;%=c.getTitle()%&gt;",                     start: "&lt;%=c.getStart()%&gt;",                     end: "&lt;%=c.getEnd()%&gt;"                 },                 &lt;%}%&gt;             ]         }); </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/Akh36.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/Akh36.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>